sea launch the sea launch venture, in which we are a 40% partner, provides ocean-based launch
services to commercial satellite customers and is reported in the l&os segment. for the year ended december 31, 2004, the venture conducted two successful launches and a third launch where the satellite reached an orbit that will meet or exceed
its expected life with the aid of its propulsion system.   we have issued
credit guarantees to creditors of the sea launch venture to assist the venture in obtaining financing. in the event we are required to perform on these guarantees, we have the right to recover a portion of the loss from other venture partners. we
believe our total net maximum exposure to loss from sea launch at december 31, 2004 totals $212 million. the components of this exposure are as follows:
